quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,178,"And leave them for a time."
  37,179,"And see, for they are going to see."
  37,180,"Exalted is your Lord, the Lord of might, above what they describe."
  43,67,"Close friends, that Day, will be enemies to each other, except for the righteous"
  43,68,"[To whom Allāh will say], "
  43,69,"[You] who believed in Our verses and were Muslims."
  44,52,"Within gardens and springs,"
  44,53,"Wearing [garments of] fine silk and brocade, facing each other."
  44,54,"Thus. And We will marry them to fair women with large, [beautiful] eyes."
  46,31,"O our people, respond to the Caller [i.e., Messenger] of Allāh{1} and believe in him; He [i.e., Allāh] will forgive for you your sins and protect you from a painful punishment.",footnotes:1:Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ).
  46,32,"But he who does not respond to the Caller of Allāh will not cause failure [to Him] upon earth, and he will not have besides Him any protectors. Those are in manifest error."
  46,33,"Do they not see that Allāh, who created the heavens and earth and did not fail in their creation, is able to give life to the dead? Yes. Indeed, He is over all things competent."
  47,22,"So would you perhaps, if you turned away,{1} cause corruption on earth and sever your [ties of] relationship?",footnotes:1:From Islām or from jihād (struggling in the cause of Allāh).
  47,23,"Those [who do so] are the ones that Allāh has cursed, so He deafened them and blinded their vision."
  47,24,"Then do they not reflect upon the Qur’ān, or are there locks upon [their] hearts?"
  48,13,"And whoever has not believed in Allāh and His Messenger - then indeed, We have prepared for the disbelievers a Blaze."
  48,14,"And to Allāh belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth. He forgives whom He wills and punishes whom He wills. And ever is Allāh Forgiving and Merciful."
  48,15,"Those who remained{1} behind will say when you set out toward the war booty to take it, ",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 9:81.],footnotes:2:[i.e., they only understood the material aspects of life.]
  49,1,"O you who have believed, do not put [yourselves] before Allāh and His Messenger{1} but fear Allāh. Indeed, Allāh is Hearing and Knowing.",footnotes:1:Rather, wait for instruction and follow the way of the Prophet (ﷺ).
  49,2,"O you who have believed, do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet or be loud to him in speech like the loudness of some of you to others, lest your deeds become worthless while you perceive not."
  49,3,"Indeed, those who lower their voices before the Messenger of Allāh - they are the ones whose hearts Allāh has tested for righteousness. For them is forgiveness and great reward."
